The paper deals with using convolutional neural networks for automatic speech recognition, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing). The paper also discusses the use of complex-valued deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the learnt acoustic model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
